sonschema-module-swagger-2 is used by registering Swagger2Module with SchemaGeneratorConfigBuilder; the module POM declares jsonschema-generator as provided rather than a normal transitive dependency.\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"kind\": \"dependency\",\n      \"coordinate\": \"io.swagger.core.v3:swagger-annotations:2.2.41\",\n      \"scope\": \"testImplementation\",\n      \"reason\": \"Meaningful coverage exercises io.swagger.v3.oas.annotations.media.Schema and ArraySchema annotations; the module POM declares swagger-annotations as provided, with 2.2.41 managed by the 5.0.0 parent.\"\n    }\n  ],\n  \"agent_guidance\": \"For version 5.0.0, victools migrated to Jackson 3. Tests that inspect generated schemas should import and use `tools.jackson.databind.JsonNode` and related `tools.jackson.databind.node.*` types, not `com.fasterxml.jackson.databind.JsonNode`. No Docker service, environment variable, or system property setup appears necessary.\",\n  \"risks\": [\n    \"Old tests copied from 4.x may fail javac if they retain `com.fasterxml.jackson.databind.JsonNode`; adding Jackson 2 is the wrong fix because the 5.0.0 API returns Jackson 3 nodes.\",\n    \"Using an older Swagger annotations version may compile for many cases but can drift from the module's managed dependency version.\"\n  ]\n}", "textSignature": "{\"v\":1,\"id\":\"msg_0b4288eb9ffce6be016a403e0460348196bc2c29990c32173a\",\"phase\":\"final_answer\"}"}], "api": "openai-responses", "provider": "OCA", "model": "oca/gpt-5.5", "usage": {"input": 417, "output": 914, "cacheRead": 31744, "cacheWrite": 0, "totalTokens": 33075, "cost": {"input": 0, "output": 0, "cacheRead": 0, "cacheWrite": 0, "total": 0}}, "stopReason": "stop", "timestamp": 1782595068563, "responseId": "resp_0b4288eb9ffce6be016a403dfd270481968665d0ecc376c10f"}, "toolResults": []}
